text.p: A king in ancient times tripped over a porcupine discovered that thier spines can find and pierce the boundaries between plate bodies. He deicded that these humble creatures might be the salvation of his empire from the demon hoard. If their spines could get past his plate body then they could also get past the tough demon scales.
He ordered his magicians to make them larger and to find a way to reinforce thier spines with cold iron. And so a new monstrosity was born...

The Sprillon are giant porcupines taht have an insatiable hunber for two things. First they hunger for iron and will eat it anywhere they can find it. They have been known to slowly knaw through the swords and armor of their victims. This hunger is driven by the need for the iron to go up and reinforce their spikes. Their second great hunger is for demons. The wizards decided to give this hunger so that it drove them towards the empires greatest enemy.

Unfortunately the habit of eating demons has warped the Sprillons over time. On one hand thier have gained a telekenetic ability allowing them to throw their spines and enabling them to take down demons much easier. The downside is that it has corrupted them so that they are both chaotic and evil. They will still take out demons... but when those are not around they will take on pigs, cows, or even humans.

list.li: Two foot tunnels with a lot of scratch marks and some iron spikes in the walls.
A fresh body pincushioned by iron needles.
